oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: First hospital in Columbia
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Photograph of a building which served as the first hospital in Columbia, Tennessee. Sections of the roof are missing, and an unidentified man is walking into the street on far left. Two typed labels adhered to the photo read: "This is the first unit of what I named W. 7th St. Office Bldgs- Added V. Lot-Hawkins Dwg Smith Dwg Cathey Off. Bldg- Profitable Property- DAD*" and "Deed to this property dated 8/23/56 Rec.11/2/56 Bk# 323 Pge 353 Deed in my Lock Bx #568-I lost $100. on option on this property 2 yrs prior."
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Hospitals; Men; Streets
